    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Ruschia uncinella are primarily based on its bioactive compounds such as flavonoids and alkaloids. A tincture is prepared by steeping the plant material in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin to create a concentrated extract. An infusion is made by steeping the dried leaves in hot water, while a decoction involves boiling the plant material in water to release its active compounds. A salve is prepared by infusing the plant material in a carrier oil to create a topical preparation, which can be used to treat skin conditions. Ruschia uncinella tea is also prepared by infusing the dried leaves in hot water, and is traditionally used to treat respiratory issues and as a diuretic.",
